gomodel:SYNGO_4105  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Fig 2B: VAC14 puncta partially colocalized with both EEA1 (23±12%) and LAMP1 (29±9%) in neurites.\nFig 2C: VAC14 also colocalises with presynaptic terminal markers synapsin, synaptotagmin and VAMP/synaptobrevin.\nFig S7D-E: The specificity of VAC14 is demonstrated by the lack of staining in VAC14 -/- KO neurons.\nFigure S1A: Specificity of anti-VAC14 antibody was verified by the absence of a band in VAC14 KO brain lysates.. Experimental description: No information on which species the hippocampal neurons are derived from. 30/09/2020 Dnyanada: Authors were contacted for species information at ude.hcimu@namsiewl" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2286-1587" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2514-0216" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-2916-7616" ;
        dc:date           "2021-01-18" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_CC_4105" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10090" .

